{
  "text": "B.V. began to feel better after pain medication, antiemetics, and IV hydration. She was discharged within 48 hours and given instructions to take in clear liquids, with slow advancement to a lowresidue diet. She was restricted from air travel for 1 week due the potential for in-flight bowel dilation [CITATION_1] . B.V. resumed her stool softener and senna and saw gradual normalization of bowel function. She was also being followed with laboratory assessment for her pancytopenia, which was not related to SBO.",
